The paper deals with a communication channel model and its capacity, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The model involves matrices and finite fields, which suggests the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the behavior of the channel for asymptotically large field size or packet length, which could be relevant to the statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-category. The optimization problem used to compute the channel capacity could be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the information-losslessness of a well-known approach, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
